If I create a class that takes a parameter in the _init method, I will get an error when trying to create an instance of a subclass of it.  Everything works fine until you call .new on the sublcass.  

In the below example I will get the error:  Invalid call to function '_init'.  Expected 1 arguments on line 27 (func _init(val) in the SubInitParam class).  If I comment out the last two lines everything works fine.  Stack trace indicates the error started at 43 (where .new is called)

You appear to be able to add parameters to _init in subclasses (SubBaseWithParameter instances work fine), but if the base has one, everything goes kaput.

``` python
extends Node2D

class BaseClass:
    var hello='w'
    func _init():
        hello='world'

class SubClass:
    extends BaseClass

    func _init():
        hello='goodbye'

class SubBaseWithParameter:
    extends BaseClass
    func _init(val):
        hello='with param:  ' + val

class BaseInitParam:
    var hello = 'asdf'

    func _init(val):
        hello = val

class SubInitParam:
    extends BaseInitParam
    func _init(val):
        hello = 'sub:  ' + val

func _ready():
    var base = BaseClass.new()
    print(base.hello)

    var sub = SubClass.new()
    print(sub.hello)

    var sub_with = SubBaseWithParameter.new('this works')
    print(sub_with.hello)

    var base_param = BaseInitParam.new('another one')
    print(base_param.hello)

    var sub_param = SubInitParam.new('yet another one')
    print(sub_param.hello)
```

This prevents you from being able to inherit from any class that has a parameter in the _init method.  
You also can't just make the sub class's _init method have no parameters.  You get the same error.

As a side note, I don't think this is restricted to just _init and inheritance.  I've seen this in other places as well but I've been able to work around them in the past.  I've currently painted myself into a corner and being able to do this would save a lot of refactoring.  

P.S.
This might be related or a separate issue, but calling .new() with the wrong number of parameters crashes the app (not the editor) with no message, just 'godot.exe has stopped working'

``` python
#call without parameter when it has one
var sub_param = SubInitParam.new()
#call with parameter when it doesn't have one
var sub = SubClass.new(1)
```

